│   return !SeenInstrs.contains(&I) && !CostCtx.skipCostComputation(&I, true);  │
│ This is the opposite of the intended logic: it only returns true if an        │
│ instruction is neither part of the VPlan nor skipped, excluding exactly the   │
│ cases the comment says should qualify (instructions that were skipped).       │
│ Consequently, if the VPlan omits or simplifies instructions but those         │
│ instructions were also marked to be skipped for cost computation (as happens  │
│ due to precomputeCosts marking induction/exit/reduction parts), the function  │
│ incorrectly returns false. This suppresses the escape hatch for legitimate VF │
